TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dynamics of Planned Organizational Change: Assessing Empirical Support For A Theoretical Model
AU  - Robertson, Peter J.
AU  - Roberts, Darryl R.
AU  - Porras, Jerry I.
Y1  - 1993/06/01
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256595
DO  - 10.5465/256595
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 619
EP  - 634
VL  - 36
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study employed meta-analytic procedures to evaluate the potential validity of a model of planned organizational change. Hypotheses derived from this model focus on the relationships among planned change interventions and three classes of organizational variables, assessing work settings, individual behavior, and organizational outcomes. The aggregated results of 52 evaluations of planned change interventions were largely consistent with the hypotheses, providing considerable support for the model as a whole. Recommendations are made for future research on organizational change evaluation.
AB  - This study employed meta-analytic procedures to evaluate the potential validity of a model of planned organizational change. Hypotheses derived from this model focus on the relationships among planned change interventions and three classes of organizational variables, assessing work settings, individual behavior, and organizational outcomes. The aggregated results of 52 evaluations of planned change interventions were largely consistent with the hypotheses, providing considerable support for the model as a whole. Recommendations are made for future research on organizational change evaluation.
